Calculate the total arc length $L$, in meters, of the trajectory of the charged compartment from the instant of ejection at $z_{\mathrm{sep}}$, until it leaves the upper boundary of the electric and magnetic field region at $z = d$ (i.e., the spatial path length traveled between $z=z_{\mathrm{sep}}$ and $z=d$ in $3$D space, considering all forces acting on the compartment). Give your answer numerically with three significant digits and the correct SI unit:

\[ \boxed{L = \;\,\underline{\hspace{8em}}\;\;\mathrm{m}} \]

