\mu_0 &= 4\pi\times10^{-7}\ \mathrm{N\cdot m^2/C^2} \\
\varepsilon_0 &= 8.8541878128\times10^{-12}\ \mathrm{F/m}
\end{align*}",
  "topic_tags": ["classical mechanics", "electromagnetism", "relativistic mechanics", "differential equations", "multi-dimensional motion", "applied mathematics"]
}

